<% content_for :page_title, "Upcase" %>

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-content">
    <h1>Take the Next Step</h1>
    <p>Upcase is an online training community for intermediate and advanced developers who aspire to continually improve their skills and knowledge.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta">
      <h5>Sign up now and join a community of <strong><%= @community_size %></strong> other developers:</h5>
      <%= link_to "View Pricing", "#price", :class => "signup" %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="features">
  <h2>What you’ll do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <div class="features-illustration">
        <div class="illustration">
          <%= image_tag "upcase/code.png", alt: "Dig into Real Code" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="features-description">
        <h3>Dig into Real Code</h3>
        <p>As a subscriber, you have access to the source code of Upcase, this application. Clone it, dissect it, change it, and participate in pull request discussions.</p>
        <p>We think Upcase is a good example of a large app with great code. It has extensive test coverage, a full implementation of SaaS billing with Stripe, and serves as an OAuth endpoint for our Discourse forum.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="features-illustration">
        <div class="illustration">
          <%= image_tag "upcase/best-practices.jpg", alt: "Learn Best Practices" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="features-description">
        <h3>Learn Best Practices</h3>
        <p>Techniques such as <a href="#">Test-Driven Development</a>, and <a href="#">Refactoring</a> help you create better code more quickly.</p>
        <p>thoughtbot is one of the leading Ruby on Rails development companies in the world. We’ve built hundreds of Rails applications, open source libraries, and we’ve followed and helped establish the best-practices of our community.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="features-illustration">
        <div class="illustration">
          <%= image_tag "upcase/vim.jpg", alt: "Master your Tools" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="features-description">
        <h3>Master your Tools</h3>
        <p>Being quick and efficient with your tools such as your editor and your shell are essential to being a better developer.</p>
        <p>Upcase features videos, exercises, and discussion around tools such as <a href="#">Vim</a> and <a href="#">Chrome Developer Tools</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="features-illustration">
        <div class="illustration">
          <%= image_tag "upcase/new-tech.png", alt: "Learn new Technologies" %>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="features-description">
        <h3>Learn new Technologies</h3>
        <p>Great developers continually explore new things which helps them grow and pick up new perspectives which can be brought back to their day-to-day work.</p>
        <p>Upcase features videos, exercises, and discussion around emerging technologies such as <a href="#">Clojure</a> and <a href="#">Haskell</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
</section>

<section class="how">
  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <div class="illustration">
        <%= image_tag "upcase/metrics.jpg", alt: "Watch One" %>
      </div>
      <div class="how-description">
        <h6 class="how-counter">1</h6>
        <h3>Watch One</h3>
        <p>Begin by watching a thoughtbot subject-matter expert take you deep within a topic during several hours of detailed videos.</p>
        <p>
          Our 5-15 minute videos include
          <%= link_to "Ping-Pong Pair Programming", "https://upcase.com/videos/ping-pong-paired-programing" %>,
          <%= link_to "RSpec Best Practices", "https://upcase.com/videos/rspec-best-practices" %>,
          and
          <%= link_to "The Art of Vim", "https://upcase.com/the-art-of-vim" %>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="illustration">
        <%= image_tag "upcase/trail.png", alt: "Do One" %>
      </div>
      <div class="how-description">
        <h6 class="how-counter">2</h6>
        <h3>Do One</h3>
        <p>You’ll follow along by coding the related exercises on your own time, on your own computer.</p>
        <p>Our Git-based system gives you your own clone to work in and push your solution to. Your instructor will answer all your questions in a chat room each week.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="illustration">
        <%= image_tag "upcase/review.png", alt: "Teach One" %>
      </div>
      <div class="how-description">
        <h6 class="how-counter">3</h6>
        <h3>Teach One</h3>
        <p>Once you’ve submitted your solution, it will be reviewed by thoughtbot and other Upcase subscribers.</p>
        <p>Submitting a solution will also allow you to review other subscribers’ solutions. We've built a custom interface for collaborative solution review.</p>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ul>
</section>

